What is unique about personal online data storage is that it is entirely up to the user who can access that type of information.
The company calls it "personal empowerment through data".
The idea for Inrupt, according to the company's HUB John Bruce, is for the company to bring resources, processes, and applicable skills to help make Solid available to everyone.
The company currently consists of Berners-Lee, Bruce, a security platform bought by IBM, developers on the staff contracted to work on the project, and a community of volunteer coders.
